On World Freedom Day, President Donald J. Trump commemorates the fall of the Berlin Wall in 1989, which marked the liberation of East Germany from Soviet communism. The event symbolized the triumph of freedom and liberty for millions of people who rejected oppression. The article highlights the United States' support for freedom and recounts the efforts to prevent the surrender of West Berlin to the Soviets. It emphasizes the importance of restoring freedom to the German people and acknowledges the sacrifices made by those who attempted to escape and those who fought against the oppressive regime. The article also mentions the United States' role in defining the Cold War and the ultimate victory of democratic principles. President Trump calls for the observation of World Freedom Day and reaffirms the commitment to combat tyranny and support those oppressed by communist regimes.